Details: I returned Brenda's call. She gave me an update. She had contacted victim support as suggested, but the lady was unable to help advised seeing doctor. She believed they needed church fellowship but due to her previous experience in Norfolk had found it difficult. However on Sunday had gone to the Methodist church near their home and spoken to some of the women following the service over tea/coffee. The minister had visited her the next day, Brenda said she was 'stunned' and 'shocked'  by the response. The minister suggested the doctor also. Brenda repeated that the trauma of previous encounter with medical proffession made it difficult if not impossible to seek medical help. She repeated feeling alone with no family or any other woman to talk to. She said she had been 'beaten' and 'abused' and 'bullied' all her life. She looked to the church to help her. I drew her attention to celebrate recovery - reading from the leaflet. (I said I was quoting) and askedif she would like me to send her leaflet.
ActionComments: Leaflet sent in post that evening. N.B. Has been looking for church since 1988, in Norfolk took it to higher authority.

Details: See Attached email. The family is really struggling and we have therefore given them a further supply of food. We offered to pray.

ActionComments: Food

It will take 2/3 months to process benefits claim for Emma and the children.  They have contacted benefit agency.  Family unable to help, have helped in the past.  Have part paid rent with last of money.  Friend unable to pick up food for them.
ActionComments: To phone back tomorrow if we are able to deliver for them.
Benefits suspended because one child gone back to birth mother. Phils father has moved due to illness and bedroom. Food given for 2 adults and 3 children.

Details: David (a jopiner) was directed by his sister. Living temporarily with daughter. Lancaster-born and bred and has family and friends here. Had private rented accommodation in Morecambe and his landlady terminated the tenancy. Went to Strategic Housing who said he was deliberately homeless as he hadn't taken his 2 months entitlement. David said her would be intimidated if he did not leave. He has no tenancy arrears.
ActionComments: Has been to YMCA and filled in an application form (rent deposit scheme). Has alcohol issues; recently been hospitalised because of alcohol-related damage. Has been in Harvey House and is trying to contact Inward House. David is dyslexic and needs help to fill forms. He is on DLA. I suggested AA and J2R. Suggested filling in housing association application for Wesley House, Sulyard St. (supported housing for over 50s); asked him to let us know his progress and to keep checking on progress with application.

Details: Called in to say thank you and to report progress. He has spoken to the new warden at Wesley House. A flat will be available soon and he will be back to see the manager.
ActionComments: He did not say whether he had completed an application. Gave him a TOB pack.

Details: Petet came in with Grahame to talk about finances. Going to DISC tomorrow but thinks he needs more help. Talked about CAP and he took a leaflet
ActionComments: Ask Hannah at CAP re; log book loans - Peter has borrowed £600 on his car log book and has to pay back £25 per week for 2 yrs.

Details: Sharon Gord phoned on behalf of the family. Jan Knowles sending someone to pick up emergency food
ActionComments: Jan came in with Michaela to collect food

Details: Recommendation from LDHAS. Called in for a 2 man tent, was in a rush, his friend calledJonathan relies on him.
ActionComments: Asked him to call back when he had more time. Won't go to Edward Sreet

Details: John is homeless as result of relationship break-up.  Returned to family in Bolton but had to leave due to a broken laptop.  His mother gave him some money for food and his benefit will be paid tomorrow - will transfer them to Lanc.  He has no alcohol/drug issues and only debt is a court fine.  Moved to Lancaster aged 13 and has friends here - can go to their's for food, shower etc.  Knows a local farmer and will pitch his tent there.  C of E but has been to Father's House - knows Dan from Soup Run.
ActionComments: Gave him advice - YMCA rent deposit scheme, registering as homeless at Strategic Housing, Morecambe, LDHAS - knows about.

Details: John called in for food - he has tried hunting and fishing with no success.  Talked about his family.  His sister takes drugs - "Bubble" (legal high).  When he was with his partner and children she broke in and robbed & set fire to his house.  His partner became depressed and he started drinking.  Does not know his real father and step-father ran away with a young Polish woman after 16 years.  Has supportive friends in Lanc.  Has provisional license and wants to take a course Lanc & Morecambe Coll to for his CS card.  Sees his children Tues and Thurs.
ActionComments: Gave him food.

Details: Asked for food. Said he did not go to LDHAS today as he had an appointment with his solicitor.
ActionComments: Benefits - he has filled in  a form which has been sent to Preston. He should receive payment next week. Hopes then to apply for his CS card. He has nothing to occuply his time and doesn't want to lose hope. Suggest courses and volunteering. He recognised they would look good on his CV. Solicitor will present his case to have his children returned - they were removed because his sister set fire to their home.

Details: Asked if we could help with food - to make sandwiches. His circumstances are unchanged. He is depressed because he feels his children willbe put up for adoption (June hearing). He feels that he is being made to 'jump through hoops' and that is he loses his children the past eight years will be pointless.
ActionComments: Suggested he registers with local doctor. LDHAS would provide a local list. Asks LDHAS to help with accommodation. He said he would go tomorrow. His former friends have seen him outside LDHAS and have spread rumours that he takes drugs. However, his drug tests have been clear. Blood tests for alcohol have not althouhg he says he is no longer drinking- has not done so since October. He goes for his third test on Monday.He is attended anger management course. He is thinking of doing the lime plastering and stonemasons course which are free. John said he had not achieved anything previously. Courses would give him a certificate. Asked if we could pray, he accepted.

Details: John asked for help with a character reference form.
ActionComments: Gave him small food pack and he is returning on Wednesday weith character reference form from YMCA re: bond.

Details: John came in to see about funding for anger management. Had a chat. He has booked for two preventing classes and is going to the training tomorrow.

John came in with Sam Lang to collect his fishing tackle.  Spoke with Kath and Sylvia about finding a free anger management course.  Looking forward to seeing his girls soon.  Seems in much better spirits and is currently staying with Paul Tomlinson.

John came in as he has a contact number for open doors. Contacted them but can only help with bond if on probation. Kath gave him information for peer support (help people suffering with depression) He will look up website in Library. He began talking about religion. His mother suggested he join the Quakers. Talked about faith matters. Invited into the inner room for hospitality and longer conversation with Sylvia.
ActionComments: John was given a cup of coffee and biscuits while we talked about what helped him to feel closer to God (in relation to different types of churches). We also talked about other faiths, and science, and John seemed to enjoy the conversation, though he had to leave as he had an appointment with his solicitor.

Details: John came in today, after being paid he had gone to the pub. He spoke to Kath, Barbara, and Sylvia about his anger towards his ex in relation to his children. He said that he had come here as he needed to tell someone how he was feeling so he would not do anything. He tried to call his mum and Grandfather, but both numbers were unavailable/engaged.
ActionComments: He talked about his faith and prayed with him and talkedto him about his faith and why bad thimgs happen. He had an appointment to pick up a letter from the solicitors accross the road, Barbara went over but was not allowed to pick it up. We gave John three glasses of water and spoke with him for a long time before he left to get the letter himself. We also gave John a prayer card: 'God give me the serenity...etc' and prayed for him after he left. Spoke to Lynette about John's anger, he was particularly violent in his speech about what he would do to his ex-partner if his children were take into care. Lynette recommended that we explain to him out responsibilities if he should come in like that again and there be a resulting or inflammatory incident etc.

Details: John asked for bread etc to make sandwiches. He has been fishing in the canal.
ActionComments: John mentioned he would come to the Maundy Thursday evening service that night at St. Thomas' where he took communion and had time to talk to the vicar. He also cam to the Ark on Friday and spoke with other guests and some of the volunteers about faith and where he sometimes struggles to believe.

Details: John came in as he had been evicted along with Paul from the house he was staying in.He asked for a sleeping bag which we couldn't provide.
ActionComments: Said we would pray for him and suggested he try Edward Street tomorrow.

Details: John asked for emergency food.
John called in for bread.  Had received food from homeless action.  Stayed for brew and chat.
ActionComments: Gave bread.
Has not gone to Bolton yet, says he's going tomorrow. Benefits stopped as he has put in a joint claim. Asked for food. Given for today and tomorrow up to lunch as he is going to Bolton!

Details: Barbara saw John at Edward Street yesterday and he called in to TOB today for a sleeping bag which we were unable to give him.  His children are waiting to be adopted - he is hoping they will stay together.  He talked about self-harm and solvent abuse.
ActionComments: Said we would pray for children.  We talked about putting the past behind him and prayed for him and his children.  He seemed calmer than when we'd seen him before.

Details: Came in with Phil Barraclough.  He asked for help with bus fare to Bolton to collect clothes.  He talked about his relationship with his mother and how it had changed for the worse.  He hoped he would be able to go to Bolton tomorrow - already had a return rail ticket.
ActionComments: Told him that we'd prayed for his 3 children.  Gave him a jacket.

Details: John called in initially for a deerstalker hat of which we had one! Plus  a scarf( unfortunately we didn't have a neck warmer) he took an ordinary scarf. Had a cuppa, chatted relaxedly about his situation. Left to catch lunch at Edward St with a quickened resolve to talk to Christin? There in the hope of getting accomodation. He expressed determination nto to go down the excess drugs and drink route. He is plannin got do a "Lettering in stone" course. Would like to eventually make a career of this.

John called in with his younger sister Rhiannon. He will be staying with his sister. He asked for help with food. He spoke about his concerns re his last meeting with his 3 children - Lucia, Summer and Dylan before adoption. Suggested he register with a local doctor to help with depression. He would lika a proper diagnosis of his mental health issues. He stated that he used substances to block out what is happening in his life, his anger, etc.

John asked for help with food. He is not staying with his sister but can go there to cook. He spoke about the anger he felt when he saw his 3 children for the last time. After Adoption Care have offered counselling but he no longer trusts them. Probation are also willing to find a counsellor. He is prepared to accept this.  He is paying back a compensation payment to an injured policeman. The incident happened 4 years ago and was assigned by the court.His own hand was cut during the incident requiring re-constructive surgery. He is still on the short list for his college course. Prayed for him before he left.
John came in for some food - he's got cooking facilities at his sister's. His benefits nt due until Monday.
ActionComments: Gave his some tins and some bread.

asked for hat and gloves. Spoke about stone-mason's course.

Details: Came for food, has now got a place in Stoneham. Told to get them to refer him to us when he needs more food.

Kath said there were positive steps and keep looking forward to make something of his life.

John came in looking better, he had been for a job interview and was hopeful he would get it. We talked about drinking, he still struggles not to drink and when he does drink he drinks until e's drunk. We talked about 'triggers'.
Gave him a bag of food. He had £40 taken out of his benefits but has now sorted it out.
Feelowship, chat.
fellowship and chat

John called in - said he'd been robbed - money due this Friday. Still waiting to get move out of Stonham.

gave him bread beans and soup but told him cant keep helping him

John asked for help with food - stayed for chat & hospitality. He is moving to Bolton - his mum has got him a flat.

John came in with Kellie Knowles, They are going to Bolton when her methadone script has been transferred. Gave them a tent & scarf each. He has had a relapse & did some gas yesterday when they had a row. Asked to have a wash.

Hospitality came in with Kellie. Went to job centre for interview

Details: Just moved to area and sorting out benefits. They have no food.

Details: Angela and Paul are still staying with Chrissy (her sister) and things are getting a bit difficult. Paul came in with Kevin. Angela has run off back to Scatland with their Giro and left hime behind with no money. We gave them some more food. He admitted he had a drink but knew the answer was not there. He is looking gorward to meal on the 22nd

Details: Referred for emergency food by YMCA. He has been homeless since he was 14 when his mum threw him out.  Father is in the forces - sees him once a week.  Mentor at YMCA is Terry.  Has a baby son - Kayleb.  He receives benefits in 2 weeks and cannot apply for crisis loan for a year.

Details: Philip called in with his partner. He is still homeless.

No longer on medication and hopes to get a new doctor at Dalton Square.  Smokes cannabis to reduce anger but is trying to stop.

Details: Phil called in and asked for help with food.  He was on his way to The Police Station to report his mugging. He has a rented room in Carnforth.

Details: Asking for help with a neighbour with alcohol problems; spoke about his own problems with depression and anxiety
Came as a result of YMCA referal for emergency food.  Has applied for a crisis loan and will receive it on Wednesday.

Details: She came from the police station and had no food, with friend Liam.  Missed her benefits.
ActionComments: Gave her a few tins.

Details: we gave food as a result of her debt
ActionComments: lisa came into Olive Branch with her mum. She was referred by Help Direct via social services. Lisa's partner has not been signing on and therefore not been receiving benefit, so she put in a claim for both of them.Due to this 'change' in circumstances the family is without money, temporaly. We gave enough food for about 3 days. Lisa has two children, the older girl lives with lisa's mum, Sue, who came in with her. This arrangement began early in Lisa's relationship with the father of her children. Lisa was 14 and her partner was 16. He is now attending 'anger management classes' with a local domestic violence service. Prayer was offered and they were very happy to have it. Took them to middle room.

Details: Additional food
ActionComments: Benefit reinstated from 24th November.  Chatted about situation noted above.  Lisa would like to have her daughter living with her, but feels that her mother is resistant to this. Encouraged again to contact CAP and to call back for another chat.

Details: We have given her food for the weekend.
ActionComments: Lisa's boyfriend has failed to sign on aid therefore they have not recieved their benefits.

Details: Lisa's partner has failed to sign on and she has now signed on in her own right.  Also she should get a cheque for her compensation claim tomorrow.
ActionComments: Gave her 1 adult 1 child pack and some bread milk and margerine.

Details: Tried to deliver hamper, twice, and phoned 3 times but to no avail. Hamper re-allocated
Referred to Joanne Wilder - Social Worker. Lisa has lost her purse - no money until Wednesday.
ActionComments: Emergency food parcel given for 4.
Food Given

Details: electricity credit
ActionComments: Yvonne was brought in by Wayne.She said that she had helped Wayne in the past with washing clothes.Yvonne asked if we could help her with electricity credit,which we did to the sum of £6.She thenaccepted prayer in the middle room, being quite touched emotionally,she would like to call in again as she doesnt have any friends near by.She has health issues she says she has been given 2 years! As a result of this is having problems with her benefits and is experiencing financial hardship.We forgot to ask her about weather she had money for food but she did say that she would call in again  on DLA stopped benefits for 8 weeks?
States she has not had water rates invoice yet. Recent diagnoses of emphsimia (her father died of this) She is trying to given up smoking . Prayer said food parcel given

ActionComments: gave emergency food    we will put money on her card if she returns tomorrow.
Dawn came back. Money put on her electricity and gas

On ESA - benefit due 17/04/2013. Son stole benefit. Son smashing-up house. No food left. Now got own bank account -can't get a Crisis Loan. Gave food parcel.

C.A.P.S.S referral. Benefits have been capped and bank charges have depleted family income.

Paul came for some food, he is living in someones drive. Barbara and I had a good spiritual chat. He was definately seeking. He is quite sporty and enjoying the weather but he does want to know more about God. He spoke about his past and his friend who had died two years ago and he was still quite emotional about it and it has impacted a lot on his life. He feelslost without his friend as they did so much together. He is active and likes canoing but doesn't want to go alone. Broke his leg twice when he was playing football as a child and died three times during a car accident when he was two. Aslo advised him to go to the CAB to find out about financial support available.
ActionComments: We gave him a little food but he is a coleac so we didn't have much to give him. We prayed for him and for healing for his coleacs disease. We gave him a welcome pack and two church easter leaflets, one for St. Tees and one for Christians Alive. Got coleacs disease - can't eat wheat or gluten.

Details: Jimmy is in a rented property with 3 others with no cooking facilities. He feels he needs to start taking medication again for his bi-polar. While in Manchester he was able to gradually withdraw all medication and felt well. He was with his brother. He returned to Lancaster for family reasons - his children. His brother has cancer of the bladder and his mother is not well. He is one of six brothers. One brother commited suicide. Jimmy is struggling at the moment and feels he is not getting the help he needs from his GP. His partner is in hospital (mental health). He has tried to support her emotionally and financially - she has not recieved her benefits yet. Suggested CAB.
ActionComments: Asked for help with food. We gave him bread, milk and a tin of tuna. Offered and recieved prayer. He repeated that he felt better.

Details: Jimmy came in for a chat. His neighbour Tony has mental issues and seems isolated. He has been in the commandos. We gave him part pack and introductary pack with 'journey into life' for his neighbour.
Jimmy, with a small child in a buggy, called in to see Barbara.
ActionComments: Told him to call in on Thursday when Barbara's here.
Benefits sactioned, missed appointment. Looking for work states he is on ESA. Moved to new flat & rented an allotment
CAP leaflet given for future reference. Witnessed about own conversion. Soon to be on the Alpha Course. Christmas food given

Details: Gordon has got into difficulty after a lady living with him has brought him into financial difficulties.  He has given CAP a ring but has not followed it through yet.
ActionComments: Gave him another leaflet and explained how CAP works.  Gave him a food parcel.

Details: Tyla came in with Joanne Finch, her Disc floating support worker.  Tyla is 18 and looking after her 14 year old brother Michael after the death of their mother.  They do not know their fathers. They lost some money and a phone on a trip to Blackpool.
ActionComments: Emergency food for Tyla and her brother.  We are here if she needs some to talk to.  We will pray.

Details: John was passing and saw our notice about addictions.  Struggling with long-term gambling addiction - 15 years old used a slot machine then got a well paid job and started casino gambling.  He always tried to cover his outgoings and set limits which he always broke.  Enjoys the excitement of risk even when he loses.
ActionComments: Gave number for university counselling service.  Info re Celebrate Recovery - brought up Catholic.  We said we'd pray.

Details: Came in looking for someone to assist him in a meeting with work - legal side.  Alan is an alcoholic who needs support in relation to his job.  Has a meeting next Wed 10am.  Done it own accord to try and sort alcoholism.  Been in UK 15 years.  Alan goes to J2R and is looking at detox and rehab.  Not sure how this will affect his but hopefully the meeting on Wed will sort out these issues.  Said he would come back to update us.
ActionComments: Gave CAP leaflet and welcome pack.  Advised him to take a friend to the meeting as we cannot.  Prayed with him for future, addiction, peace and hope. Texted info about TLC Resettlement project at LDHAS.

Details: Phone Referral from Alice: Child Protection Socail Services, White Cross.

Details: TA for 3 months. David had seperated from his wife and 4 children approx 18 months ago due to his drink problem. He did intimate that he is very different (angry?) when drunk.
ActionComments: Suggested he visit Strategic Housing (not sure if he had done or where he was up to with this) as he has lived in the area all his life. We had a chat about God and he believes. I chatted to him about my testimony and invited him to church.He seemed quite open and said he would coome.

He is depressed because of the situation and is on anti depressents but does not want to take them. He has suffered from depression before. His mother died when he was 17 and his father at 24. He feels the loss of his sister from ovarian cancer, angry that his brother in law found someone else so soon.
